com.motorola.mod

Class ModInterfaceDelegation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.motorola.mod.ModInterfaceDelegation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Parcelable

    public class ModInterfaceDelegation
extends Object
implements Parcelable
    A class represents the Linux device node corresponding to the greybus interface. A device on the Moto Mod will be available through a greybus interface and the kernel will create a device node to represent this device, applications communicate through this interface delegation and the data will be transimited via the greybus connection to the device on the Moto Mod.

    The ModInterfaceDelegation class should primarily be used by application when retrieving the Interface delegation for a Raw channel. 

     List<ModInterfaceDelegation> rds =
          mManager.getModInterfaceDelegationsByProtocol(devices.get(0),
          ModProtocol.Protocol.Raw);
